Other myths say Èṣù was primordial too — present at the very beginning as the principle of movement, crossroads, and communication.

In short: Òbàtálá is usually “first creator of humans,” Òrúnmìlà is “witness to destinies,” Èṣù is “cosmic operator of paths.”



